# .cursorrules
project:
  name: "Secure Cross-Platform VPN Client"
  description: "Flutter-based VPN client using Xray-core and sing-box with dynamic SOCKS5 authentication"
  tech_stack:
    - Flutter (Dart)
    - Xray-core (Go)
    - sing-box (Go)
    - Platform channels (Android: Kotlin/Java, iOS: Swift, Windows/Linux/macOS: C++/Go via FFI)
  security_requirements:
    - No open SOCKS5 proxy on localhost without authentication.
    - Implement per-session random username/password for SOCKS5 (dynamic credentials).
    - Never hardcode or log credentials.
    - Destroy credentials after VPN stop.
    - All local proxy listeners must be bound to 127.0.0.1 and require authentication.
    - Use split tunneling only with proper isolation (no bypass via localhost scanning).
  architecture:
    - Core engines: Xray-core and sing-box as separate binaries or libraries.
    - Switchable engine at runtime.
    - Flutter UI communicates with native engine via platform channels (or go-flutter plugin).
    - VPN tunnel setup using Flutter VPN plugins (e.g., v2ray_box, wireguard_flutter_plus).
  coding_guidelines:
    - Follow effective Dart style guide.
    - Write unit tests for credential generation and validation.
    - Document any platform-specific code.
    - Use Flutter Riverpod or Bloc for state management.
  ai_assistance_preferences:
    - Provide code snippets with full imports.
    - When explaining, highlight security implications.
    - Prefer solution using v2ray_box plugin as baseline.
    - When generating configuration JSON for Xray/sing-box, include "inbounds" section with "auth": "password" and dynamic credentials.
    - For native integration, show how to pass credentials from Dart to Go binary via stdin or environment variables.
  known_vulnerability_context:
    - March 2026: widespread vulnerability in Hiddify, v2rayNG, Happ etc. due to unauthenticated local SOCKS5 proxy (port 7890). Any app could read real IP and configs.
    - Our solution must be immune: no listening on 0.0.0.0, always require auth, rotate credentials per session.